article.headline: UC Santa Barbara 69, Fresno St. 54
article.story: SANTA BARBARA, Calif. -- Orlando Johnson scored 35 points Saturday night to lead UC Santa Barbara to a 69-54 victory over Fresno State. Johnson also grabbed 11 rebounds for the Gauchos (2-2). He made 13 of 19 shots from the field, including 4 of 5 from behind the 3-point arc. He had 23 points in the first half, one more than the Bulldogs, as UC Santa Barbara took a 35-24 halftime lead. James Nunnally added 12 points and six rebounds for the Gauchos, who made 51 percent of their shots from the field. Greg Smith led Fresno State (1-2) with 15 points and eight rebounds. The Bulldogs were within seven points with 3:57 to go, but were outscored 12-4 the rest of the way.
